etymologies: mid 16th century; earliest use found in Nicholas Udall (1504–1556), schoolmaster and playwright. From pate + -ed

definitions: Having a head (especially the crown of the head) or mind of a specified kind.

notes.text: Frequently as the second element of compounds: compare "bald-pated", "clod-pated", "curl-pated", muddle-pated, etc.
